%20is%20severe%20trauma%20at%20home%2C%20such%20as%20alcoholism%20or%20abuse%2C%20children%20%26quot%3Beither%20pull%20apart%20so%20they%20have%20no%20connection%20to%20each%20other%20or%20they%20pull%20together%20for%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20question%20Dr.%20Lewis%20asks%20patients%20is%20whether%20they%20were%20close%20to%20their%20siblings%20as%20young%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20namely%20from%20birth%20to%20the%20age%20of%20eight%20or%20nine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20ages%20are%20critical%20in%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20gets%20recreated%20many%20years%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20It's%20also%20easier%20to%20fix%20a%20conflict%20when%20there's%20some%20semblance%20of%20foundation.%20If%20not%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20to%20create%20something%20new%20that%20was%20never%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESiblings%20often%20reconnect%20later%20in%20life%20after%20a%20period%20of%20distance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20feeling%20like%20a%20relationship%20has%20become%20superficial%20to%20total%20cutoff%2C%20estrangement%20exists%20on%20a%20spectrum%2C%20Dr.%20Lewis%20explained.%20But%20there's%20often%20hope%20if%20the%20relationship%20isn't%20completely%20severed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20study%2C%20she%20said%20she's%20observed%20an%20%26quot%3Bhourglass%20pattern%2C%26quot%3B%20whereby%20kids%20are%20close%20growing%20up%2C%20then%20become%20distant%20into%20adulthood%20as%20they%20establish%20their%20own%20professional%20lives%20and%20families.%20But%20later%20in%20life%2C%20they%20often%20come%20back%20together%20as%20they%20leave%20the%20workplace%2C%20their%20children%20grow%20up%2C%20and%20their%20parents%20pass%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20her%20work%2C%20she%20said%2C%20occurs%20with%20patients%20who%20have%20experienced%20a%20crisis%2C%20like%20the%20death%20of%20a%20parent%2C%20which%20precipitates%20reconciliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20looking%20for%20some%20advice%20ahead%20of