20a%20Kerala%20woman%2C%20who%20is%20on%20death%20row%20in%20Yemen%20for%20killing%20a%20Yemeni%20national%2C%20to%20travel%20to%20the%20West%20Asian%20country%20to%20negotiate%20blood%20money%20with%20the%20victim's%20family%20and%20save%20her%20daughter%20from%20the%20gallows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Subramonium%20Prasad%20directed%20the%20Centre%20to%20relax%20its%202017%20notification%2C%20which%20barred%20Indian%20passport%20holders%20from%20travelling%20to%20Yemen%2C%20for%20the%20petitioner%20subject%20to%20her%20filing%20an%20affidavit%20that%20she%20will%20travel%20with%20another%20person%20to%20the%20restive%20nation%20to%20negotiate%20her%20daughter's%20release%20at%20her%20own%20risk%20and%20responsibility%20without%20any%20liability%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20or%20the%20state%20government%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20High%20Court%20took%20note%20of%20the%20Centre's%20submission%20that%20India%20does%20not%20have%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Yemen%2C%20has%20closed%20its%20embassy%20there%2C%20and%20that%20no%20international%20treaty%20is%20applicable%20in%20the%20present%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20hearing%20a%20plea%20by%20Prema%20Kumari%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20Nimisha%20Priya%2C%20seeking%20facilitation%20of%20her%20travel%20along%20with%20three%20others%20to%20Yemen%20to%20negotiate%20compensation%20with%20the%20victim's%20family%20to%20save%20her%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYemen's%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20November%2013%20dismissed%20the%20appeal%20of%20Nimisha%20Priya%2C%20who%20was%20working%20as%20a%20nurse%20in%20the%20West%20Asian%20country%2C%20against%20her%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Priya%20has%20been%20convicted%20of%20murdering%20Talal%20Abdo%20Mahdi%2C%20who%20died%20in%20July%202017%2C%20after%20she%20injected%20him%20with%20sedatives%20in%20order%20to%20get%20back%20her%20passport%20from%20his%20possession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20alleged%20that%20she%20administered%20the%20sedatives%20so%20she%20could%20take%20back%20her%20passport%20while%20he%20was%20unconscious%20but%20he%20died%20of%20an%20overdose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Priya's%20mother%20moved%20the%20High%20Court%20earlier%20this%20year%20seeking%20permission%20to%20go%20to%20Yemen%20in%20spite%20of%20a%20travel%20ban%20for%20Indians%20and%20negotiate%20the%20blood%20money%20to%20save%20her%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20Centre's%20counsel%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20the%20government%20had%20issued%20a%20notification%20on%20September%2026%2C%202017%20stating%20that%20an%20Indian%20passport%20holder%20cannot%20travel%20to%20the%20troubled%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20that%20clause%203%20of%20the%20notification%20gives%20power%20to%20the%20government%20to%20relax%20its%20provisions%20for%20specific%20and%20essential%20reasons%20for%20which%20a%20limited%20time%20may%20be%20granted%20by%20the%20central%20government%20at%20the%20express%20request%20of%20the%20applicant%20who%20will%20travel%20at%20their%20own%20personal%20risk%20without%20any%20liability%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20observed%20orally%20why%20should%20there%20be%20so%20much%20reluctance%20on%20the%20Centre's%20part%20for%20a%20mother%20making%20a%20last%20attempt%20to%20save%20her%20daughter%20from%20the%20gallows.%20Advocate%20Subhash%20Chandran%20KR%2C%20who%20represented%20the%20petitioner%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20other%20person%20who%20will%20be%20travelling%20with%20the%20mother%20has%20a%20valid%20visa%20for%20Yemen%20and%20is%20working%20there%20for%20more%20than%2024%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner's%20counsel%20said%20they%20will%20be%20travelling%20at%20their%20own%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20that%20the%20man's%20affidavit%20said%20he%20is%20ready%20to%20travel%20with%20Nimisha%20Priya's%20mother%20to%20Yemen%20to%20help%20her%20negotiate%20with%20the%20authorities%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20view%20of%20the%20affidavit%2C%20this%20court%20is%20inclined%20to%20direct%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20to%20relax%20the%20notification%20of%202017%20for%20the%20petitioner%20on%20her%20filing%20an%20affidavit%20to%20the%20effect%20that%20she%20will%20be%20travelling%20to%20Yemen%20with%20the%20other%20person%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20negotiating%20for%20the%20release%20of%20her%20daughter%20at%20her%20own%20personal%20risk%20and%20responsibility%20without%20any%20liability%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India%20or%20the%20state%20government%20concerned.%E2%80%9D%20The%20court%20asked%20the%20petitioner%20to%20file%20an%20affidavit%20giving%20the%20dates%20of%20travel%20and%20return%20and%20disposed%20of%20the%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20counsel%20for%20Ms%20Priya's%20mother%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20the%20Yemen's%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20on%20November%2013%20dismissed%20her%20appeal%20and%20upheld%20the%20death%20sentence%2C%20gave%20her%20a%20last%20option%20of%20escaping%20the%20gallows%20by%20securing%20a%20pardon%20from%20the%20victim's%20family%20after%20paying%20blood%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner's%20lawyer%20had%20said%20a%20letter%20informing%20the%20family%20about%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Yemen%20dismissing%20Priya's%20appeal%20was%20received%20on%20December%201%20and%20her%20execution%20can%20take%20place%20anytime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20'Save%20Nimisha%20Priya%20International%20Action%20Council'%20had%20approached%20the%20high%20court%20last%20year%20and%20sought%20direction%20to%20the%20Centre%20to%20%26quot%3Bfacilitate%20diplomatic%20interventions%20as%20well%20as%20negotiations%20with%20the%20family%20of%20the%20victim%20on%20behalf%20of%20Nimisha%20Priya%20to%20save%20her%20life%20by%20paying%20blood%20money%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%20in%20a%20time-bound%20manner%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20alleged%20Mr%20Mahdi%20had%20forged%20documents%20to%20show%20he%20and%20Ms%20Priya%20were%20married%20and%20abused%20and%20tortured%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20High%20Court%20had%20earlier%20refused%20to%20direct%20the%20Centre%20to%20negotiate%20payment%20of%20blood%20money%20to%20save%20Ms%20Priya's%20life%20but%20asked%20it%20to%20pursue%20legal%20remedies%20against%20her%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702403880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fas3jduj_kerala-nurse-nimisha-priya-_625x300_17_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-high-court-allows-kerala-woman-to-travel-to-yemen-to-save-daughter-on-death-row-4660534%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20permitted%20the%20mother%20of%20a%20Kerala%20woman%2C%20who%20is%20on%20death%20row%20in%20Yemen%20for%20killing%20a%20Yemeni%20national%2C%20to%20travel%20to%20the%20West%20Asian%20country%20to%20negotiate%20blood%20money%20with%20the%20victim's%20family%20and%20save%20her%20daughter%20from%20the%20gallows.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-high-court-allows-kerala-woman-to-travel-to-yemen-to-save-daughter-on-death-row-4660534%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-high-court-allows-kerala-woman-to-travel-to-yemen-to-save-daughter-on-death-row-4660534%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-high-court-allows-kerala-woman-to-travel-to-yemen-to-save-daughter-on-death-row-4660534%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Infosys%20saga%3A%20A%20leadership%20facto