est.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJoram%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Devashish%20Makhija%E2%80%99s%20fourth%20directorial%20feature%2C%20fashions%20a%20grim%20political%20drama%20as%20a%20Western%20thriller.%20Mostly%20set%20in%20a%20mineral-rich%20village%20occupied%20by%20tribals%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20the%20film%20takes%20place%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20land-grabbing%20corporates%20propped%20up%20by%20local%20governments%2C%20patronising%20middle-men%2C%20violent%20rebel%20forces%2C%20and%20common%20folk%20engulfed%20and%20overwhelmed%20by%20them%20all.%20In%20a%20key%20scene%2C%20Dasru%20confronts%20a%20police%20informant%2C%20who%20pleads%20for%20his%20life%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20help%20the%20police%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20labelled%20%E2%80%98Naxal%20sympathisers%E2%80%99%20and%20thrown%20in%20jail.%20If%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20help%20the%20rebel%20forces%2C%20they%20hang%20us%20upside%20down%20for%20being%20bootlickers.%20We%E2%80%99re%20screwed%20from%20both%20sides.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FXOCbjto_DFk%3Fsi%3DCyukRc0PGwIBQF03%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20film%20that%20relies%20on%20Piyush%20Puty%E2%80%99s%20marked-with-character%20visuals%20%E2%80%93%20like%20transmission%20towers%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20nowhere%20%E2%80%93%20allowing%20viewers%20to%20feel%20rather%20than%20be%20told%2C%20the%20conversations%20(written%20by%20Makhija)%20are%20stinging.%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20no%20one%20fighting%20anymore%3F%E2%80%9D%20bemoans%20Dasru%2C%20only%20to%20be%20told%20that%20fighting%20feeds%20the%20soul%2C%20but%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20do%20much%20for%20the%20stomach.%20When%20Dasru%20is%20asked%20about%20why%20he%20ran%20away%2C%20he%20objects%2C%20saying%20he%20ran%20away%20from%20the%20gun%2C%20not%20the%20village%20%5BDasru%20was%20a%20Naxal%20militant%2C%20before%20escaping%20to%20Mumbai%5D.%20When%20a%20Mumbai%20cop%20asks%20a%20constable%20in%20Jharkhand%20how%20they%20%E2%80%9Ccommunicate%E2%80%9D%20without%20proper%20mobile%20coverage%20in%20the%20rural%20areas%2C%20the%20constable%20responds%20%E2%80%9CAdjust%20%3Cem%3Ekar%20lete%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20sir%20%5BWe%20try%20to%20adjust%2C%20sir%5D%E2%80%9D%2C%20his%20face%20telling%20a%20million%20unspoken%20tales.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJoram%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20named%20after%20Dasru%E2%80%99s%20three-month-old%20baby%20who%20is%20tied%20to%20his%20back%20as%20they%E2%80%99re%20on%20the%20run%2C%20kicks%20off%20during%20a%20chance%20encounter%20in%20Mumbai%20when%20a%20tribal%20minister%20from%20Jharkhand%20%E2%80%93%20Phulo%20Karma%20(Smita%20Tambe%2C%20with%20a%20distressing%20stare)%20%E2%80%93%20is%20distributing%20sarees%20and%20she%20recognises%20Dasru.%20He%E2%80%99s%20grown%20his%20hair%20and%20changed%20his%20name%20%5Bhe%20calls%20himself%20Bala%20in%20Mumbai%5D%2C%20but%20Karma%20has%20the%20knowing%20eyes%20of%20a%20predator%20having%20spotted%20her%20next%20kill.%20Staging%20Vaano%E2%80%99s%20murder%20and%20implicating%20Dasru%20for%20it%2C%20Karma%20ensures%20Dasru%E2%80%99s%20face%20is%20circulating%20on%20social%20media%20in%20no%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20socio-political%20critiques%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20always%20an%20overwhelming%20unpleasantness%20in%20Makhija%E2%80%99s%20films.%20Especially%20how%20he%20never%20pulls%20his%20punches%20while%20depicting%20bad%20behaviour.%20Remember%20when%20he%20showed%20the%20villain%20in%20%3Cem%3EAjji%3C%2Fem%3E%20raping%20a%20mannequin%2C%20with%20his%20barely%20human%20qualities%3F%20The%20writer-director%20seems%20to%20have%20rectified%20that%20by%20rooting%20%3Cem%3EJoram%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20antagonist%20in%20grief.%20Phulo%20Karma%20is%20driven%20by%20revenge%3B%20loneliness%20fuels%20her%20quest%20to%20kill%20Dasru.%20Makhija%20establishes%20this%20with%20two%20brisk%20scenes%2C%20when%20Karma%20wakes%20up%20from%20a%20nightmare%2C%20and%20when%20she%20asks%20a%20subordinate%20to%20eat%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20conscience%20of%20%3Cem%3EJoram%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20Mohammed%20Zeeshan%20Ayyub%E2%80%99s%20Ratnakar%20Bagul.%20Ayyub%20never%20overplays%20his%20hand%20as%20the%20upright%2C%20honest%20cop%20%E2%80%94%20navigating%20a%20jungle%20of%20superiors%2C%20politicians%20with%20vested%20interests%2C%20subordinates%20putting%20their%20lives%20at%20risk%20for%20him%2C%20realising%20getting%20out%20of%20the%20web%20he%E2%80%99s%20being%20sucked%20into%20will%20need%20all%20of%20his%20quiet%20resolve.%20There%E2%80%99s%20an%20ease%20with%20which%20Ratnakar%20excuses%20himself%20from%20vile%20celebrations%2C%20setting%20locked-up%20minors%20free%2C%20and%20the%20way%20he%20keeps%20telling%20the%20local%20cops%20to%20%E2%80%98not%20shoot%E2%80%99%2C%20despite%20being%20given%20orders%20to%20kill%20Dasru%2C%20rather%20than%20capture%20him%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMakhija%E2%80%99s%20films%20(%3Cem%3EAjji%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EBhonsle%3C%2Fem%3E)%20have%20always%20felt%20righteous%20in%20their%20anger%2C%20by%20getting%20protagonists%20to%20avenge%20the%20system%E2%80%99s%20deficiencies%20in%20his%20films%E2%80%99%20climax.%20In%20%3Cem%3EJoram%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit%20almost%20feels%20like%20the%20director%20might%20be%20losing%20hope%20in%20revisionist%2Ffantastical%20endings%2C%20when%20someone%20comes%20and%20sets%20things%20right%20(on%20however%20small%20a%20scale).%20It%20appears%20like%20the%20filmmaker%20has%20made%20his%20peace%20with%20society%20%5Band%20by%20extension%20the%20film%20ecosystem%20for%20independent%20filmmakers%20like%20him%5D%20being%20beyond%20help.%20No%20amount%20of%20initiative%2C%20however%20extraordinary%2C%20will%20displace%20the%20rich%2