2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12142857%2F4321532715_27a62fa02f_c.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12142857%2F4321532715_27a62fa02f_c-300x233.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688833%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22284%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBenjamin%20Zephaniah.%20Photo%3A%20David%20Morris%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20rare%20claim%20about%20a%20city%20where%20the%20currents%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20contemporary%20culture%20inevitably%20wash%20up.%20During%20that%20visit%2C%20Zephaniah%20described%20himself%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgriot%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20travelling%20poets%2C%20musicians%2C%20and%20storytellers%20in%20West%20Africa%2C%20who%20are%20also%20often%20the%20oral%20historians%20of%20their%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20was%20a%20poet%20for%2024%20hours%20of%20the%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20poet%20Vivek%20Narayanan%2C%20who%20met%20him%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20Mumbai%20around%20the%20same%20time.%20%E2%80%9CHe%2C%20of%20course%2C%20performed%20but%20rejected%20the%20division%20between%20published%20and%20performed%20poetry.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarayanan%2C%20the%20author%20of%20several%20books%20%E2%80%93%20including%20%3Cem%3EAfter%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%2C%20a%20modern%20retelling%20of%20the%20Ramayan%20%E2%80%93%20explains%20that%20in%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%2C%20performance%20poetry%20had%20a%20very%20specific%20social%20and%20cultural%20context.%20While%20established%20mainstream%20poets%20had%20books%20from%20publishers%20like%20Faber%20and%20others%2C%20performance%20poets%20were%20usually%20working-class%20or%20Black%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20Zephaniah%20did%20not%20really%20see%20publishing%20and%20performance%20as%20a%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20came%20out%20very%20strongly%20when%20I%20interviewed%20him%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20Bombay%20(Mumbai).%20He%20had%20performed%20some%20impromptu%20poems%2C%20which%20was%20part%20of%20his%20conception%20of%20being%20a%20poet.%20You%20needed%20to%20have%20poetry%20inside%20you.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mumbai%2C%20Zephaniah%20performed%20on%20the%20lawns%20of%20the%20iconic%20David%20Sassoon%20Library.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20reading%20might%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20turning%20points%20of%20how%20performance%20poetry%2C%20which%20was%20not%20very%20well-known%20in%20India%20then%2C%20was%20thought%20about%20in%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoet%2C%20novelist%20and%20translator%20Jerry%20Pinto%20also%20remembers%20attending%20the%20reading%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20back%20garden%20of%20the%20David%20Sassoon%20Library.%20Background%20accompaniment%20provided%20by%20the%20adolescent%20impatience%20of%20Mumbai%20traffic.%20Faint%20night%20chill%20of%20faux%20winter.%20Whiff%20of%20hand-rolled%20cigarettes.%20Benjamin%20Zephaniah%20whipped-whupped-whopped%20at%20us.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20remember%20the%20set%2C%20I%20remember%20the%20impact%2C%20the%20poetry%20not%20spoken%2C%20not%20recited%2C%20but%20lived.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View-1024x768.jpg%2010